Quote: he [Hongi] presented it to me the moment he got on board, ... <i>Ibid.</i> 53 The war-mat [so tightly woven, that when hanging loose a spear will not penetrate it] is generally ornamented with a border, which frequently displays a great degree of taste: the Vandyke is a common pattern.
