Date: 15/9/1864
Source: Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: "With their war-mats on."   The natives formerly made a thick matted sort of cloth, impervious to spear-thrusts, which they used as armour.   In more modern times this defence was only used to save the breast from injury in climbing trees.
Notes:

